    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="467" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Runyon</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 12,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department is advised that Louis Stern, having come to New York to-day to
                            consult friends as to course he is to pursue, receives telegrams to-day
                            that Bavarian Government is about to issue immediate execution of
                            sentence. He asks intervention of the Department to procure from
                            Bavarian Government postponement of execution for not less than sixty
                            days. You will at once endeavor to do what you can to obtain compliance
                            with this reasonable request.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
